text: Meroux-Moval is a commune. It is found in the region Bourgogne-Franche-Comté in the Territoire de Belfort department in the northeast of France. The municipality was created on 1 January 2019 and consists of the former communes of Meroux (the seat) and Moval.Arrêté préfectoral == References == Category:2019 establishments in France Category:Communes in Territoire de Belfort
